# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath9
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah paced back and forth through the throne room."
    new "Sarah paced back and forth through the throne room."

    old "Except for her, there was nobody. Each step echoed through the vast room."
    new "Except for her, there was nobody. Each step echoed through the vast room."

    old "Xan had met with her shortly at the start of the day."
    new "Xan had met with her shortly at the start of the day."

    old "They had discussed strategy, he had offered some words of comfort, but in the end there wasn't much else he could offer."
    new "They had discussed strategy, he had offered some words of comfort, but in the end there wasn't much else he could offer."

    old "She was here, alone."
    new "She was here, alone."

    old "Near the far side of the throne room, the only gate that lead to the royal quarters had been barricaded."
    new "Near the far side of the throne room, the only gate that lead to the royal quarters had been barricaded."

    old "Nobody was getting through here."
    new "Nobody was getting through here."

    old "Echoes had begun to ring out over Bagrad."
    new "Echoes had begun to ring out over Bagrad."

    old "Shouting, explosions, screams."
    new "Shouting, explosions, screams."

    old "None of it told Sarah anything about which way the battle was going. Only that the battle was still raging."
    new "None of it told Sarah anything about which way the battle was going. Only that the battle was still raging."

    old "A great roar of some kind rang out."
    new "A great roar of some kind rang out."

    old "Did the Mythrans have cannons? Sarah wasn't sure."
    new "Did the Mythrans have cannons? Sarah wasn't sure."

    old "Sarah forced herself to sit down, hoping that if she calmed her body, it might calm her mind."
    new "Sarah forced herself to sit down, hoping that if she calmed her body, it might calm her mind."

    old "She forced everything from her mind."
    new "She forced everything from her mind."

    old "Only the moment mattered. Only this moment mattered."
    new "Only the moment mattered. Only this moment mattered."

    old "So long as she remembered that creed, life could be so simple. Guard a room, that was all there was to it."
    new "So long as she remembered that creed, life could be so simple. Guard a room, that was all there was to it."

    old "Like a mantra, she passed the phrase through her mind, again and again, until it was all there was."
    new "Like a mantra, she passed the phrase through her mind, again and again, until it was all there was."

    old "Clattering of metal."
    new "Clattering of metal."

    old "Sarah opened her eyes."
    new "Sarah opened her eyes."

    old "The room was still empty, but the sound had been different."
    new "The room was still empty, but the sound had been different."

    old "It sounded like it came from inside the palace."
    new "It sounded like it came from inside the palace."

    old "Sarah stopped her own breathing and listened."
    new "Sarah stopped her own breathing and listened."

    old "More noises rang out. Fighting. Inside the palace."
    new "More noises rang out. Fighting. Inside the palace."

    old "Had they lost the battle? Had the Mythran army made its way inside?"
    new "Had they lost the battle? Had the Mythran army made its way inside?"

    old "No, it couldn't be. Xan would have come back for her."
    new "No, it couldn't be. Xan would have come back for her."

    old "Unless he died."
    new "Unless he died."

    old "Sarah shook her head. It would take more than that for her mentor to die."
    new "Sarah shook her head. It would take more than that for her mentor to die."

    old "More sounds, the fighting drew closer. Shouts of soldiers echoed through the halls."
    new "More sounds, the fighting drew closer. Shouts of soldiers echoed through the halls."

    old "They were coming. Her hopes of getting through the day without any violence were over."
    new "They were coming. Her hopes of getting through the day without any violence were over."

    old "She reached out her arms and gathered the magical energies around her. It had been years since her training began, and it now felt like a second nature."
    new "She reached out her arms and gathered the magical energies around her. It had been years since her training began, and it now felt like a second nature."

    old "Seizing on the currents, Sarah leapt up and by her will, gravity inversed."
    new "Seizing on the currents, Sarah leapt up and by her will, gravity inversed."

    old "Falling upwards, her feet lifted from the floor, and Sarah observed the world below her."
    new "Falling upwards, her feet lifted from the floor, and Sarah observed the world below her."

    old "The shouting grew louder. They were close."
    new "The shouting grew louder. They were close."

    old "Suddenly, the door to the throne room was thrown open and a surge of soldiers streamed in."
    new "Suddenly, the door to the throne room was thrown open and a surge of soldiers streamed in."

    old "Sarah could see them searching the room, but none considered to look up. She had the advantage."
    new "Sarah could see them searching the room, but none considered to look up. She had the advantage."

    old "Everyone, into the throne room!"
    new "Everyone, into the throne room!"

    old "Keep pushing, the path to western wing should be close."
    new "Keep pushing, the path to western wing should be close."

    old "Sarah pulled in the the magical energies, allowing them to rush through her body, overflowing."
    new "Sarah pulled in the the magical energies, allowing them to rush through her body, overflowing."

    old "She opened her mouth and began to sing."
    new "She opened her mouth and began to sing."

    old "The song of the pale flame."
    new "The song of the pale flame."

    old "A pale blue light errupted from her eyes and mouth, a crackling sound like lightning roared through the throne room."
    new "A pale blue light errupted from her eyes and mouth, a crackling sound like lightning roared through the throne room."

    old "All at once, the soldiers in the room looked up towards the ceiling and saw her."
    new "All at once, the soldiers in the room looked up towards the ceiling and saw her."

    old "Bright, radiant, deadly."
    new "Bright, radiant, deadly."

    old "A scream rang out, the way an animal might try to warn the herd, but it was too late."
    new "A scream rang out, the way an animal might try to warn the herd, but it was too late."

    old "From her elevated position, Sarah lunged downwards, launching herself towards the ground."
    new "From her elevated position, Sarah lunged downwards, launching herself towards the ground."

    old "The pale flame, pure condensed magical energy, flowed from her body, warped into the shapes of her will, tracing behind her."
    new "The pale flame, pure condensed magical energy, flowed from her body, warped into the shapes of her will, tracing behind her."

    old "With the sweep of her hand, she brought the pale fire down like a lash."
    new "With the sweep of her hand, she brought the pale fire down like a lash."

    old "Striking a group of three soldiers before they could react, the lash cut them in half before they could utter a scream."
    new "Striking a group of three soldiers before they could react, the lash cut them in half before they could utter a scream."

    old "Sarah spun around, her hand commanding the energy with a natural ease, and the lash sliced through another group, splattering their bodies to red mist."
    new "Sarah spun around, her hand commanding the energy with a natural ease, and the lash sliced through another group, splattering their bodies to red mist."

    old "So hot did the pale flame burn, that their blood instantly boiled and condensed, filling the room with the smell of slaughter."
    new "So hot did the pale flame burn, that their blood instantly boiled and condensed, filling the room with the smell of slaughter."

    old "She had only just begun."
    new "She had only just begun."

    old "Sarah could see the soldiers running, screaming, trying to understand what they had to do."
    new "Sarah could see the soldiers running, screaming, trying to understand what they had to do."

    old "They had been trained to fight in battles against other soldiers, few knew anything about magic, other than to run away."
    new "They had been trained to fight in battles against other soldiers, few knew anything about magic, other than to run away."

    old "But they couldn't run away, for the throne room had only one way out, and Sarah would not let them."
    new "But they couldn't run away, for the throne room had only one way out, and Sarah would not let them."

    old "Thrusting her hand forward, the pale flame shifted and reshaped, shooting out like pellets, she perforated a soldier who tried to aim a crossbow at her."
    new "Thrusting her hand forward, the pale flame shifted and reshaped, shooting out like pellets, she perforated a soldier who tried to aim a crossbow at her."

    old "Behind her, she felt an arrow strike close, only to be caught in one of her magical wards."
    new "Behind her, she felt an arrow strike close, only to be caught in one of her magical wards."

    old "With the grace of a dance, she spun her body around and snapped her finger at him, causing a pillar of flame to errupt underneath the crossbowman. He died screaming."
    new "With the grace of a dance, she spun her body around and snapped her finger at him, causing a pillar of flame to errupt underneath the crossbowman. He died screaming."

    old "She could hear the footsteps of a man rushing her."
    new "She could hear the footsteps of a man rushing her."

    old "Sarah leapt up and with magical tendrils, kept herself suspended above the ground."
    new "Sarah leapt up and with magical tendrils, kept herself suspended above the ground."

    old "With the sweep of an arm, the lash sliced through the brave soldier, cutting him off above the waist."
    new "With the sweep of an arm, the lash sliced through the brave soldier, cutting him off above the waist."

    old "Caleb! NOOO!"
    new "Caleb! NOOO!"

    old "She knew that name."
    new "She knew that name."

    old "Where did she know it from..."
    new "Where did she know it from..."

    old "There wasn't time, she couldn't allow herself to be distracted."
    new "There wasn't time, she couldn't allow herself to be distracted."

    old "Sarah opened her mouth and continued her magical song. Death rained down all around her as the pale flame swept and warped, cutting apart the soldiers."
    new "Sarah opened her mouth and continued her magical song. Death rained down all around her as the pale flame swept and warped, cutting apart the soldiers."

    old "By now, there was no resistance left."
    new "By now, there was no resistance left."

    old "She could see the soldiers scramble, running, hiding. There was nobody left to fight her."
    new "She could see the soldiers scramble, running, hiding. There was nobody left to fight her."

    old "She brought her hand down and doused another soldier in piercing fire. He burned, holding the corpse of another."
    new "She brought her hand down and doused another soldier in piercing fire. He burned, holding the corpse of another."

    old "Lifted by the magical tendrils, Sarah slowly drifted through the air, seeking out what few soldiers remained."
    new "Lifted by the magical tendrils, Sarah slowly drifted through the air, seeking out what few soldiers remained."

    old "It was a soft culling, as soft as such a thing could be."
    new "It was a soft culling, as soft as such a thing could be."

    old "She didn't want them to suffer. No more than they needed to. She didn't love the power she held over ordinary people."
    new "She didn't want them to suffer. No more than they needed to. She didn't love the power she held over ordinary people."

    old "Suddenly, a familiar voice rang out."
    new "Suddenly, a familiar voice rang out."

    old "SARAH!!!"
    new "SARAH!!!"

    old "The voice cut through the murder. Sarah felt her distant demeanor slip."
    new "The voice cut through the murder. Sarah felt her distant demeanor slip."

    old "She spun around in the air towards the voice and saw her."
    new "She spun around in the air towards the voice and saw her."

    old "Her old friend."
    new "Her old friend."

    old "Sarah...what did you do..."
    new "Sarah...what did you do..."

    old "Who was she."
    new "Who was she."

    old "Who was she to come here, after all these years, and question her."
    new "Who was she to come here, after all these years, and question her."

    old "The girl who she thought was her friend. The one who robbed her of her home, stole her away across an ocean, and forever changed her life."
    new "The girl who she thought was her friend. The one who robbed her of her home, stole her away across an ocean, and forever changed her life."

    old "The thief. The drunkard. The traitor."
    new "The thief. The drunkard. The traitor."

    old "Who do you think you are to question me about anything?"
    new "Who do you think you are to question me about anything?"

    old "Sarah could see the radiant light that she cast, shimmering, cutting through the darkness. She illuminated everything."
    new "Sarah could see the radiant light that she cast, shimmering, cutting through the darkness. She illuminated everything."

    old "The pale light brought out Kate's features. The fear in her face."
    new "The pale light brought out Kate's features. The fear in her face."

    old "Sarah...why did you do that?"
    new "Sarah...why did you do that?"

    old "Because I am here on a mission. To guard this place from low-lives that would seek to loot it."
    new "Because I am here on a mission. To guard this place from low-lives that would seek to loot it."

    old "You killed Caleb...and Ephraim..."
    new "You killed Caleb...and Ephraim..."

    old "The names sounded familiar. A lifetime ago. Kind men. Had she really snuffed out their lives so casually?"
    new "The names sounded familiar. A lifetime ago. Kind men. Had she really snuffed out their lives so casually?"

    old "And who are they to me?"
    new "And who are they to me?"

    old "Nobodies. People that I might have known years ago."
    new "Nobodies. People that I might have known years ago."

    old "A lot has changed, as you might notice."
    new "A lot has changed, as you might notice."

    old "Sarah could see the magical energies crackle around her, emphasizing her power."
    new "Sarah could see the magical energies crackle around her, emphasizing her power."

    old "You're a freak..."
    new "You're a freak..."

    old "Maybe. But it took me a long time to find my way back to myself after what you did to me. When you stabbed me in the back."
    new "Maybe. But it took me a long time to find my way back to myself after what you did to me. When you stabbed me in the back."

    old "Don't deny it, Kate. Save yourself and myself the disgrace of lying."
    new "Don't deny it, Kate. Save yourself and myself the disgrace of lying."

    old "Sarah could see Kate struggle to find the words."
    new "Sarah could see Kate struggle to find the words."

    old "Kill Kate"
    new "Kill Kate"

    old "Sarah raised up her hands towards her old friend, magical energies twisting around her arms, ready for the kill."
    new "Sarah raised up her hands towards her old friend, magical energies twisting around her arms, ready for the kill."

    old "You used my trust in you, and you betrayed me."
    new "You used my trust in you, and you betrayed me."

    old "You thought because I was just some spoiled noble girl, you could use me and treat my life like it meant nothing."
    new "You thought because I was just some spoiled noble girl, you could use me and treat my life like it meant nothing."

    old "I never sought revenge against you, but you've brought yourself here."
    new "I never sought revenge against you, but you've brought yourself here."

    old "Any last words?"
    new "Any last words?"

    old "Sarah could see Kate had none."
    new "Sarah could see Kate had none."

    old "Kate did not run, fight or beg. It would have made no difference, but still, she did not."
    new "Kate did not run, fight or beg. It would have made no difference, but still, she did not."

    old "Sarah snapped her fingers."
    new "Sarah snapped her fingers."

    old "Kate died in flame."
    new "Kate died in flame."

    old "So intense did the fires burn that soon only ash and soot were left of her."
    new "So intense did the fires burn that soon only ash and soot were left of her."

    old "Then, the last of the soldiers followed her in death."
    new "Then, the last of the soldiers followed her in death."

    old "Sarah stepped down back onto the ground."
    new "Sarah stepped down back onto the ground."

    old "A dominating silence hung over the room. Ashes slowly drifted across the floor."
    new "A dominating silence hung over the room. Ashes slowly drifted across the floor."

    old "Spare Kate"
    new "Spare Kate"

    old "Sarah lowered her arms."
    new "Sarah lowered her arms."

    old "Despite everything, she couldn't do it."
    new "Despite everything, she couldn't do it."

    old "Take the rest of your soldiers and leave, before I change my mind."
    new "Take the rest of your soldiers and leave, before I change my mind."

    old "Sarah watched as Kate turned to gather the soldiers and exit the throne room."
    new "Sarah watched as Kate turned to gather the soldiers and exit the throne room."

    old "Neither spoke another word to the other."
    new "Neither spoke another word to the other."

    old "The room was empty."
    new "The room was empty."

    old "After repelling the last of the soldiers, nobody else came to try again."
    new "After repelling the last of the soldiers, nobody else came to try again."

    old "Maybe it was only a small advance party, or maybe rumors spread of the mad mage that guarded this room."
    new "Maybe it was only a small advance party, or maybe rumors spread of the mad mage that guarded this room."

    old "Whatever it was, Sarah had succeeded."
    new "Whatever it was, Sarah had succeeded."

    old "She sat down on the steps that led up towards the throne and looked out across the throne room."
    new "She sat down on the steps that led up towards the throne and looked out across the throne room."

    old "Traces of her magic could be seen across the room, but it wasn't anything some servants wouldn't be able to fix."
    new "Traces of her magic could be seen across the room, but it wasn't anything some servants wouldn't be able to fix."

    old "Sarah breathed in."
    new "Sarah breathed in."

    old "The smell of ash and burned blood was heavy in the air."
    new "The smell of ash and burned blood was heavy in the air."

    old "All this power."
    new "All this power."

    old "She had given up so much to gain it, made it her goal in life, and yet it never made her happy."
    new "She had given up so much to gain it, made it her goal in life, and yet it never made her happy."

    old "Being able to end a life with little more than a gesture, made taking it feel like a small thing. It made people seem like small things."
    new "Being able to end a life with little more than a gesture, made taking it feel like a small thing. It made people seem like small things."

    old "Sarah began to understand how Xan, having done this for centuries, could have turned so cold."
    new "Sarah began to understand how Xan, having done this for centuries, could have turned so cold."

    old "Would she?"
    new "Would she?"

    old "Had she already?"
    new "Had she already?"

    old "Sarah tries to clear her mind, sitting amidst the ashes."
    new "Sarah tries to clear her mind, sitting amidst the ashes."

